One of life's most cruel and twisted laws is that the worst of things can and will always happen to the best of people.

Scott, I barely knew you, and yet I am compelled to honor you. Smart, approachable, amicable. You didn't deserve it. I hope that the kid who did this to you will be tried as an adult and prosecuted to the fullest extent of the law. I wish peace upon your family and friends.

Rest in peace, Scott. You will be sorely missed.

Closed until further notice. 

Sorry.

Thanks.

Michael Titus graduated Jupiter High School two years ago. He has been in the army for seven months, and was stationed at Fort Benning, for airborne training. He was given a 4 day break that began last Friday. During his break, he either spent time with his family, or was with our battalion. He went with the drill team on Saturday to cheer us on, and he came to our picnic Sunday to hang out and share stories. Everybody knew Mike. Everybody liked Mike.

Today, the Colonel got a call from Mike's mother. Mike died on Monday while driving back to Fort Benning, as a result of a car accident. Everybody who knows Mike is devastated. Nobody could have foreseen what happened yesterday. He was only 20 years old.


From everyone at the Jupiter Warrior Battalion: Thank you, Mike. Rest in peace. We'll miss you.






<center>In Loving Memory:</center>
<center>Private First Class Michael Titus</center>
<center>1986-2006</center>
<center>Soldier, Son, Friend</center>

i have no will to update anymore, and no motivation to do so.

this journal is terminated until further notice.

i hate math. i think i have or am going to have a 'c' in that class soon. lovely.

definately entering in the 'Sunshine State Games'. woo. i could use a new blade.

this week is out last REAL week of school. it's just exams after this. that's weird.

ran a mile in gym. i detest running.

then fencing. beat up on the new ones. that never gets old.

and now i'm off to do something stupid. joy.

goodnight

i almost forgot.

i got a book in the mail the other day from the US Fencing Association about the 'Sunshine State Games'. should i enter? what do you guys think?

today started with me waking up and feeling like i got into a fight with a really angry kangaroo. something must be up with the food at the golf club. i remember the morning after the military ball i felt sick. but that was a little worse. maybe i'm building up a resistance.

anyway, i took a shower, then slept some more. read all my old journal entries, then occupied myself until 5. went out to get some dinner and upgrade a couple free baseball tickets. 

dad and i went to rodger dean, and that was fun. we always end up having a good time there. AND i made 10 bucks. i always win when i bet against him at baseball.

and now i'm currently singing along to 'Smooth Criminal' and having a pretty good time doing it.

ahhhhh that's happy.

--later

went over to Ryan's this afternoon for practice. no practicing got done, but that's a given.

band banquet. pretty fun i guess. not really a dancing person, but i still found ways to embarrass myself. i'm so proud.

it was mostly a sad thing, though. reminded me of all the seniors leaving. everyone got up and did their little speeches. some were funny, most were pulling on everybodies heart strings (if that's how the phrase goes, i can't remember). attempted to dance. didn't look so good. but i did manage to get down at the end with that little running man thing. and a sloppy moon-walk. i need to practice that.


Jessica: wow. right when i get to know you, you go and leave on me. lol. i'm going to miss you, so visit often! FSU won't know what hit them.

Lindsay: thanks for the rose or tulip or whatever it is! i love ya!

Ryan: hooray for breakdancing! i'm giving you the title of 'Grand Master of Funk'. i don't know why. just be proud.

i feel a tear coming on. i hate mood swings. especially when they try and break my 4-year-or-however-much-it-was record.

goodnight

i just watched 'Starsky and Hutch' and it's one of the best movies ever.

all i did today was lay on the couch and neglect my math homework because i'm sick. i feel dirty and rushed.

umm..........

you put the lime in the coke, you nut and drink them both together.

now to do math homework.......in a few hours or so.

--cough

so spring practice is tomorrow. i'm excited.

i get to meet all my little incoming-freshies :)

'The Flame' by Cheap Trick is a really good song. listen to it if you ever get the chance.


this is stolen from a dear friend of mine. his name is Paulie Paulie Four Fingers and he has a shoulder problem. rock on, Paul.

We all have things about our friends that make us slightly envious. Not in a bad way, but in a "Wow! I wish I had that person's hair, eyes, money, relationship, toe nails whatever."

So tell me what about me makes you envy me, then post this in your LJ and see what makes me envious of you.

if you feel a strong urge to post anonymously, then do so.


i'm gonna go waste time. 

--later

Billy Idol concert. two words:

FREAKING AMAZING

that was one of the best concerts i've been to. and it was only 20 bucks! i can't get over the radicalness of Billy Idol. i got a t-shirt :) i will be displaying it on monday.

anyway, i went to band 'practice'. actually, we got alot done. first we dicked around and listened to music, then Ryan played 'Santeria' and i figured out a snare part for it. then Brian showed up late and we were transposing music when i had to leave for Sunfest. cool stuff.

ok, before i go into my day,

now on to my day.

bio: DNA extraction lab. making necklaces and hanging our DNA from them. i feel like i'm being initiated into a cult.

english: still did nothing.

ROTC: banged my head against a wall for several minutes. then spun a rifle.

now i get to do a big packet on factoring so that i might be able to go to Ryan's for practice. woo.

Nina, along with the drum circle, got robbed (i honestly didn't think the Wazoo's were that good). AND MR. SANZ SANG! i admire him. i don't think he's gonna live this one down though.

we played football today in ROTC. i love physical fridays. Doug plowed one of my defenders into the ground, and when i go to bump him off one of my guys, he whines at me. 'lay off man!'. i was soooooooo close to giving him push-ups. that was annoying.

a weekend without homework! wooooooooooooooooo!

IT'S EARTH DAY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

i almost forgot! eeeeeeeee!

in honor of earth day, here's a song dealing with pollution in America, sung to the tune of what else, but 'America the Beautiful'.

'Oh beautiful
for smoggy skies,
for insecticided grain,
for strip mined mountain majesties,
above the asphalt plane.
America! America!
man sheds his waste on thee.
and hides the pines with billboard signs,
from sea to oily sea.'

not to deface a national song, but it's good for protest, no?

ok, NOW i'm gonna go do something.

--later

ok, so practice got cancelled. boo.

BUT i'll be at the talent show. yay!

today went like this:

biology: read something about anti-bacterial soap. wtf?!

band: i guess we're playing in the spring concert? woo.

first half of geometry: took the first half of my test. easy :)

lunch: decided to sit with the cool people (Lindsay, Jessica, Brian). notice how i didn't mention Zach Rives. why? because he's an asshole. p.s. the car that you described can't go anywhere near that fast. get your facts right before you lie about them, dickhead.

'yeah, i got drunk before the homecoming parade, blah blah blah'. whatever. your ass was sober, i saw you. if you were even close to being that drunk, you couldn't have supported your tuba, and you would have been on the ground when the parade was over.

why don't girls like you, you ask? (he was seriously asking this in band). let's see. 

1) you're a chauvenist and a womanizer and you're proud to admit it! honestly, why on earth would you brag about stuff like that???

2) you smell HORRIBLE. 10 out of 10 peers agree. get your ass in a shower, you stink.

3) people sort of don't like it when you insult them on a regular basis. crazy, right?

ok, i'm not gonna say any more, i'm done with you. for now.

second half of geometry: took the second half of the test. still easy :)

gym: jogged five laps. played basketball.


and now i'm drained. from what, i have no idea.

i'm gonna unwind.

--love to most

i did my leadership audition today. i don't think i'll make it. he seems to dislike the fact that i'm an underclassman. and he's pressuring me to take the HIGHLY OVERPRICED lessons that Mrs. Sanz is offering. sorry dude, but if it's 20 bucks a half hour, it's not happening. 

but he said some really nice things about me (which boggled my mind) so that was cool.

i've been inducted into 'Death By Cable'! yesssssssss! we're practicing tomorrow. i'm excited.


courses i applied for next year:

AP biology
pre-AP english II
pre-AP world history
health/driver's ed
algebra II honors (ugggggg)
ROTC II
wind ensemble
french I (as a backup)

woo.

i was in charge of flag detail today and Cody bitched about me having a constituted position of authority, so I made him run. far. i love it!

wow, my room looks like a crime scene. i should go clean it. 'should' being the key word. later!

a sincere batch of congratulations to some cool people:

1) Jessica! who as of yesterday was accepted into the FSU school of music, making me a very proud little armadillo. i'm soooo happy for you!

2) Pope Benedict XVI, who began his 'Popehood' today.

and

3) Troy, for getting suspended AGAIN!

if i have overlooked anybody for their achievements, please let me know so i can issue 'props' accordingly.


so Mr. Sanz signed me for wind ensemble...though when he hears me audition, i'll probably get sent to concert band.

i love Joe.

and i'm too lazy to write anything else. maybe later. maybe.

LTM day tomorrow. THANK GOD!

a nice day today. not too shabby.

drill was fun. we did exhibition for about 30 minutes and then played football for the rest of the time. i got tackled twice. sorta like, rolled over on my neck. ow. Majuan tackled me into the little raised part of the field (we were playing in that little bowl shaped thing by the band room) and i landed on my shoulder and all 230 pounds of Majuan's bulk was on me. it was disturbing. i never EVER want to get that close to him again.

now i have grass stains in my shirt. sadness.

fencing tonight, and that means fresh meat :) that'll be great.

i must cleanse myself. Majuan got me all dirty. ewwwwwwww.

ahem...WOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOHOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!

kay, wind ensemble, you guys ROCKED!


Jessica: that solo was awesome. the wind that was blowing gave it an awesome visual effect too. very cool.

Emily: ok.........you mean to tell me that you memorized that whole solo? that's insane. but quite impressive. definately worth a superior with distinction.

Mr. Sanz is hilarious. all you guard girls were awesome.

i could complain about the color guard, but i'm not going to.

back to the band though.

i had to leave after the last song and i definately owe some people hugs (TWO hugs for some people. you know who you are *shifts eyes*).

so if you want to collect, the First National Bank of Patrick will be open all week during normal business hours. if you're one of the first 20 people to open an account, you will recieve a free toaster!

i'm gonna go to bed now. goodnight all.

CORPORAL!!! yessssssss!
that's radical.

so last night i had to watch the dogs. boring stuff.
then i called Lindsay and we talked for a while. fun stuff.
then i slept. good-for-your-body stuff.

woke up this morning and went to the drill team barbecue. we played rugby, which is better than football, and then got thrown around by the waves. those waves were big, rough, and angry. but i wore my sunglasses while we were in the water and they never fell off. i love my little cheap sunglasses. aaaand i got promoted. it was happy.

so now i'm waiting to go to the kravis center. woo!

soooooo i'll see you cool cats later? yeah.

drill team barbeque and kravis center (go wind ensamble!) tomorrow. woo.

the pep rally was...unenthusiastic? i guess.

made me miss marching season. lol, i'm such a geek.


everybody's working today! boo. then again, i guess am too. being self-employed rocks!

i loooooove "Thriller".


******* ***** must die. painfully.


"Bohemian Rhapsody" is a great song too.


i'm gonna play with sharp objects. later.

today was funny and enjoyable.

biology: Brian and I presented. everybody loved the powerpoint because we got it to play margaritaville through the whole presentation. it was beautiful.

weightlifting: worked out, messed around with jeff and paul and trevor and alex. fun stuff.

first half of english: new teacher loved my essay. said she was scared of me because i have my black belt and that i want to be a bounty hunter along with private investigating or being a detective. it was happy.

lunch: alex kydd + large amounts of alcohol + late night tv commercials = hilarity in mass quantities. poked Lindsay. saw Jessica (yay)!

second half of english: had an enjoyable discussion about 'Great Expectations'.

ROTC: watched yet another movie (chain reaction?). heard some things that made me happy. found out Sergeant Major was featured in a Tom Clancy book (radical)! got to be in charge of the flag detail (yessss). ate donuts.

it was a lovely day.

now i'm depressed and tired for no reason at all. how lame. 

dudes and dudettes, let us do something tomorrow night. Patrick desires a social life.

guess who's ranked 33 out of 866 freshmen? me!

imagine that! i'm in the top 4%. that's cool.

i must watch the dogs. later.

*sigh*

well...

where to start...

today was a bipolar day. everything minus the anger.

mr. sanz is happy for once with how we play. we're actually sounding really good.

i got a 63 on my math test. at least my parents aren't angry...

i had a vision and a dream last night. i know it means something, and it might happen, i don't know. if it does, it's gonna be scary. but looking at it from a cinematic point of view, it was really freaking cool.

i'm not gonna be all dramatic. i don't like it and neither do you guys.

so i'm gonna help jessica with her homework i guess. if i can go out.

peace

don't you just love death threats?

i sure do. i get a real kick out of them.

they actually think i'm afraid to die.

psshhh.

like i have anything to live for anyway.


now on to something else.

well...nothing else, actually. nothing happened today. i said it was a good day in my last entry, but i guess that really wasn't true. it was just an average day i guess.

the best parts were the death threat, and of course, the following:

we were bringing in the flags in ROTC, and i'm just walking with the squad, everythings slow and normal. and then i see Lindsay walking across the courtyard. and being the weird ass that i am, i decided to follow her all stealth-like.

so she stops at one of those bench things and i'm about 30 feet away, and she's looking at a gecko in a bush, so i walk up right behind her so i'm like an inch away and put my head right next to hers and she didn't even notice! stood there for like a minute, then just as i was about to say something she moved again, so i tapped her on the shoe or something and she was all scared and stuff. it was amusing.

and i'm sure i sound like a dumbass and that a second grader could have explained that better than i did, but at this point, nothing really matters.

i get my math test back tomorrow. pray for me.

i'm gonna try and manipulate my sixth sense. worth a try, right?

i'm beginning to dislike the human species again. i guess nothing lasts forever.

i'm out

owwww.....

ok. to all you guard girls out there. 

MAD PROPS!

i mean like, insanely mad 'we should canonize these girls' props.

because let me tell ya:

spinning a rifle is freaking hard.

at least for a guy like me. who up until now has only spun spaghetti onto a fork. and has difficulty with it.

i bring this up because the ROTC drill team is now doing exhibition drill. and sasha is teaching us! that's happy.

so she taught me a little basic spinny thing that i can embarrass myself with. but i spun it seven times once! and i was proud. then i could only do it two times. then three. then one. then i'd do something stupid and drop it.

i was trying to do some movement that turner was teaching with the 15 pound rifle, and the butt plate caught me on the side of my elbow sorta hard and it sorta hurt. oww.

but it's all good. 

pretty sure i did bad on my math test...the geometry honors department is satan.

they made us draw a pentagram. i'm gonna sue. just to piss them off.

well, i'm gonna be lazy.

love
